  "AI content payment is not merely a copyright or transaction-efficiency problem; it is a question of political-economic legitimacy. As AI valuations reach hundreds of billions, society asks why the gains from public web content and human knowledge accrue to a few firms. The paper proposes a six-layer tiered data market — from free public content through scarce verified datasets to public benefit-sharing — and defines the AI network democratic economy: rights, pricing, participation, auditability, and returns, each democratized through machine-readable protocols like AICR/AICL.": "Pambayaran konten AI mboten namung babagan hak cipta utawi efisiensi transaksi; menika pitakenan legitimasi politik-ékonomi. Sarehne penilaian AI dumugi atusan milyar, masarakat pitaken kenging menapa kauntungan saking konten web umum saha kawruh manungsa mlebet dhateng namung sawetara perusahaan. Makalah menika ngusulaken pasar data kanthi tataran nem-lapis — saking konten umum gratis, liwat dataset ingkang dipunverifikasi lan langka, ngantos pambagi manfaat umum — saha netepaken ékonomi jaringan demokratis AI: hak, panentuan reregan, partisipasi, kemungkinan audit, saha asil, ingkang saben-sabenipun dipundemokratisasi liwat protokol ingkang saged dipunwaos mesin kadosta AICR/AICL.",
