  "AICL is the licensing and transaction layer built on top of AICR. Where AICR declares what is allowed, AICL defines how permission is actually obtained: license tiers and prices, quote and payment endpoints, signed license tokens, usage and audit logs, and revocation. It is designed to interoperate with emerging machine-payment mechanisms such as HTTP 402 flows and pay-per-crawl schemes, with agentic payment kept inside human-approved budgets and audit trails.": "AICL minangka lapisan lisensi saha transaksi ingkang dipundamel ing sadhuwuring AICR. Menawi AICR ndeklarasiaken punapa ingkang dipunlilani, AICL netepaken kadospundi idin menika sabenaripun dipunpundhut: tataran lisensi lan reregan, endpoint kanggé penawaran saha pambayaran, token lisensi ingkang dipuntandhatangani, log panganggé lan audit, saha pambatalan. AICL dipunrancang supados saged interoperasi kaliyan mékanisme pambayaran mesin ingkang saweg tuwuh, kadosta alur HTTP 402 saha skema pay-per-crawl, mawi pambayaran agentik ingkang tetep wonten ing salebeting anggaran saha jejak audit ingkang dipunsetujoni manungsa.",
